status_message:
Muhammadu Buhari took Nigeria’s oath of office on Friday, assuming the presidency of Africa’s most populous nation in a ceremony that marked a historic transfer of power on the continent.

U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry, and scores of African presidents, and diplomats from across the world watched as Mr. Buhari took over from Goodluck Jonathan, who in March became the first ever Nigerian president to lose an election. 

Brass bands, two R&B singers and a gospel choir performed in what concluded a rare peaceful transfer of leadership.
link_name: Nigeria’s Buhari Sworn In as President in Historic Transfer of Power
